column5: Kevin and I flew in to Eddie North's Camp at Windsor Lake. On Saturday we unpacked and got the camp ready. We only fished for four hours andgot three pike in the low 40's. Didn't get another big pike until Friday....we got twomore in low 40's. Monday night it rained for 27 hours. Sunday through Thursdaywe caught hundreds of average size pike and walleye.Overall we had a great trip. Thanks Mike and Eddie.http://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...tte101/023.jpgPike 42"http://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...tte101/021.jpgSmall Pike were sure hungryhttp://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...tte101/020.jpg100's of Pikes caught like thishttp://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...tte101/018.jpganother big Pikehttp://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...e101/012-1.jpgKevin with a nice Walleyehttp://i313.photobucket.com/albums/l...e101/007-2.jpgThat;s what 27"s of rain looks like!

Your welcome sir and thank you aswell,we have put the water system and shower in last week.We have a group of 6 in there right now and our guide tells us they are landing 100 walleyes a day per boat and a few lunker pike in there too.
See you in a few days Eh!
